translations.fi:
Applicants applying with non-Finnish qualifications must send the required enclosures to their first-preference UAS admission services by 10 February 2015 by 3:00 p.m. Finnish time (UTC+2) at the latest.

Required enclosures:
• copies of the original degree certificates (high school/secondary school)
• authorised translation of the certificate if needed (in English, Finnish or Swedish, the translation must have the translators' signature and stamp)
• NON-EU/EEA Citizens: English language proficiency certificate

If you are an EU/EEA citizen, you are able to apply even if your degree certificate is completed during the spring of applying (secondary school certificate).

translations.fi:
Application attachments

Intake 2015

Please, send your attachments by post in good time because the speed of postal services varies a lot in different countries. The postmark on your attachment package is not taken into account: It will NOT be sufficient. It is your responsibility to make sure that all attachments arrive at the Admission Office by the closing date. All attachments arriving after the closing date will not be considered.

1) Copies of certificates

Applicants with a Finnish qualification

If you are a candidate for the Finnish matriculation examination, you apply with your latest upper secondary school certificate, you do not need to send copies of your certificates as the UAS will receive the results of your matriculation examination directly from the Matriculation Examination Board.

If you apply with a Finnish competence-based further vocational or specialist vocational qualification, you must submit copy of your original certificate to the Admissions Office of the UAS of your first choice by the 10th of February 2015 3.00 pm at the latest.

If you are completing an IB-examination in a Finnish upper secondary school in the spring 2015, you must submit a copy of your Predicted Grades to the Admissions Office of the UAS of your first choice by the 15th of May 2015 Finnish time (+2 hrs GMT).


Applicants with a non-Finnish qualification

If you apply with a non-Finnish qualification, you must submit copies of your original certificates to demonstrate your eligibility to UAS studies. This does not apply to you if you are a citizen of an EU/EEA-country and you are completing your qualification in the spring of applying.

The copies must arrive at the Admissions Office of the UAS of your first choice by the 10th of February 2015 at 3.00 pm Finnish time (+2 hrs GMT). The UAS accepts only final certificates awarded by national and regional bodies granting educational certificates. Therefore other documents such as "Testimonials", "Statements of Results", "Examination Results" or "Result Slips" are not considered as official certificates.

If you are a refugee or in a refugee-like situation and you cannot prove the qualifications you have obtained through documentary evidence, the UAS can consider, whether you can be invited to the entrance examination. You must prove your refugee status by decision made by a competent authority and send a copy of the decision to the Admissions Office of the UAS of your first choice by the 10th of February 2015 at 3.00 pm Finnish time (+2 hrs GMT).

 

2) Translations of certificates

If your certificate is not written in Finnish, English or Swedish, you must also enclose certified translation of your certificate into Finnish, English or Swedish translated by a licensed translator. The translations must have translator’s signature and stamp on them.

The translations of the certificates must arrive at the Admissions Office of the UAS of your first choice by the 10th of February 2015 at 3.00 pm Finnish time (+2 hrs GMT).

 

3) Certificate of language skills

If you are applying with a non-Finnish qualification and you are not a citizen of an EU/EEA-country, you must provide proof of your English language skills to demonstrate your eligibility to UAS studies by sending a certificate of your language skills to the Admissions Office of the UAS of your first choice by the 10th of February 2015 at 3.00 pm Finnish time (+2 hrs GMT). You must provide one of the following minimum requirements:

  • an IELTS score academic level 6.0. Order your IELTS Test Report (Getting my results). The test result is valid for two years.
  • a TOEFL score 550 paper-based test / 79 - 80 internet-based test. TOEFL score results are only accepted directly from the Educational Testing Service (= ETS). When you take the test, you will have to designate the institutions you would like to receive your score reports. The Designated Institution (= DI) code for Lapland UAS is 4992.  After taking the test you can order additional official score reports for institutions you did not identify in the test. The test result is valid for two years.
  • a Cambridge ESOL’s Certificate of Proficiency in English (CPE) or Cambridge ESOL’s Certificate in Advanced English (CAE) CEFR level C1 or Cambridge IGSCE Certificate level C
  • a Pearson Test of English General level 4 or Academic overall score 51. The PTE General certificate is valid permanently. The PTE Academic score report is considered valid for two years and only if it is accessed via the Pearson score report website.
  • skills level 4 in English in all subtests (reading comprehension, listening comprehension, writing and speaking) in the National Certificate of Language Proficiency by the Finnish National Board of Education. The certificate is valid permanently.
  • an upper secondary school education in English or a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree completed in English and completed in Great Britain, Ireland, the United States, Canada, Australia or New Zealand. The language of education can be seen in your certificate. No other countries will be considered.
  • a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree conducted in English in an EU/EEA-country
